US-based Nigerian musician Adeyinka Hazzan known as Yinka Rythmz has released a new single to appreciate his family, friends, fans and social media followers who have been supportive of his career. The single, titled ‘The Appreciation,’ according to him, is a super vulnerable song that appreciates his past and present. The song itself is executively produced by Rashan Music International in collaboration with Top Dreams Universal. The Appreciation (Memoir) was recorded in Maryland, USA. -Advertisement- The music video was shot and edited by the multi-award-winning international Africano Media and is directed by OSM production, Oluwasegun Oyegbile who also produced the new single. The distinct sound of fuji in Yinka Rythmz’s voice infused with the new school Afrobeats and Afro cultural sound makes the song stand out.